design for exploration arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe featured archive gallery design for exploration design for exploration is a first time course taught jointly between stanford art department faculty john edmark and the san francisco exploratorium design for exploration is a first time course funded by a sica curricular innovation grant taught jointly between stanford art department faculty john edmark and sebastian martin from the san francisco exploratorium during the course students investigated and experimented with all aspects of the creation of interactive museum exhibits students attended on site exhibit floor sessions prototyping workshops and lectures from museum staff on exhibit design during the course students designed and constructed exhibits for temporary placement on the floor of the exploratorium art department website jason chuang sica photographer 2009 2010 home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
